examples.en: We don't want to rouse any suspicions.
I have my suspicions about his motives.
Their suspicions egged them to cruelty.
The evidence amply (or fully) confirms our suspicions.
The tests confirmed the doctors' suspicions of cancer.
His remarks played to the suspicions of the committee.
These suspicions are confirmed by the most direct proof.
The expression on his face confirmed me in my suspicions.
The note aroused her suspicions that he was having an affair.
The mother's deviate response to her child's death aroused suspicions.
Her tendency to be secretive only serves to legitimate their suspicions.
